For test validity, please record a video of yourself collecting a saliva sample and dropping the sample to the Test Card. You should record the whole process and make sure you are as clearly visible as possible in the video.

For self-recording: place your device in a stable position where the camera faces directly at you. 
We do not recommend recording a video with holding the device in one hand while taking a test.
When recorded by someone else: please make sure the video is not to shaky and clearly shows your face.
While the video is being recorded, collect saliva with the tip of the tongue and spit it directly in the buffer tube up to the indicated line.
Put the filter cap tightly onto the tube. Mix by turning upside down 10 times.
Apply the mixture to the sample hole until it is completely filled. (minimum 2-3 drops)
